<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION CARRIERS: ROCKWELL - GENERAL PROCEDURES - INSTALL OLD DRI-LOC FASTENERS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1400609" svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
        <title>INSTALL OLD DRI-LOC FASTENERS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean the oil and dirt from threaded holes. There is no special cleaning required and it is
                not necessary to remove the old Dri-Loc adhesive from threads.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply four or five drops of Loctite 277 to threaded holes ONLY. Make sure the adhesive is on
                the threads (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400646">Figure 46</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400646" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400646" filename="../figg14/G1400646.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 46. Apply Loctite to Threaded Holes</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Do not apply adhesive to the fastener threads. Air pressure in the hole will push the adhesive
                        out as the fastener in installed.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the fasteners to the required torque value for that size fastener. Refer to the
                <hotlnk document="s14006t_57.xml" xrefid="hl1400608">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>
                for the correct torque value (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400647">Figure 47</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400647" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400647" filename="../figg14/G1400647.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 47. Tighten Fasteners</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>There is no drying time required for Loctite 277.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
